    <text type="correspondence">
        <body>
            <div1>
                <pb facs="ccda.corr00209.001.jpg"/>

                <fw type="letterhead" place="top-left" hand="#h01">CHAS. W. CHESNUTT<lb/>1005
                    WILLIAMSON BUILDING<lb/>CLEVELAND, O.</fw>

                <dateline><add hand="#h02">Cleveland,<date when="1905-09-16">September 16,
                    1905.</date></add></dateline>

                <opener hand="#h02"> <address>
                    <addrLine> Horace Traubel, Esq.,</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>1624 Walnut Street,</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>Philadelphia, Pa.</addrLine>
                    </address> 
                    
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Traubel:&#8212;<ref type="editorial" resp="#slg"
                    target="Traub"/></salute> </opener>

                <p hand="#h02">My daughter Helen<ref type="editorial" resp="#csm" target="hmc"
                    />, who was visiting recently in Philadelphia, tells me that she came very near
                    meeting you, but was called home by a telegram the day before she would have had
                    that pleasure. She has given me a couple of photographs which I think Mr.
                    Bolivar<ref type="editorial" resp="#csm" n="3" target="wcb"/> handed to her, and
                    for which I thank you very much. It is a pleasure to look upon even the
                    counterfeit presentment of the face one of whom I have learned to esteem from
                    his writings, and who at the same time has shown his appreciation of my own. I
                    hope to meet you personally before very long.</p>

                <p hand="#h02">I see from the Conservator<ref type="editorial" resp="#slg"
                    target="Conserv"/> that the Walt Whitman<ref type="editorial" resp="#as" 
                    target="Whit"/> books can be obtained from you. I should like to have a copy of
                    the popular edition of Leaves of Grass<ref type="editorial" resp="#csm"
                    target="LoG"/>, and a volume of <add hand="h03" place="supralinear">your
                    own</add><add hand="h03" place="below">^</add> Chants Communal<ref
                    type="editorial" resp="#csm" target="Chants"/>. I enclose money order for
                    $2.25, which I hope includes sufficient for the postage.</p>


                <closer> <salute hand="#h02">Yours sincerely,</salute> <signed hand="#h03">Chas. W.
                    Chesnutt.</signed></closer>


            </div1>

        </body>

    </text>

